{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-settings.json"
}

/*
SETTINGS.LOCAL.JSON - Personal Project Settings
===============================================

Location: .claude/settings.local.json
Purpose: Personal overrides for this specific project
Commit: NO - This file is automatically gitignored by Claude Code

WHAT THIS FILE IS FOR
=====================

This is YOUR personal configuration for this project. It overrides
the team-shared settings.json with your preferences.

Use this for:
1. Personal permission overrides
2. Local environment variables
3. Personal tool preferences
4. Machine-specific settings

WHAT TO PUT HERE
================

PERSONAL PERMISSIONS:
- Commands you personally want auto-approved
- Overrides to team permission settings
- Personal shortcuts and aliases

Example:
{
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "Bash(my-personal-script *)",
      "Bash(my-alias *)"
    ]
  }
}

PERSONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:
- API keys for local development
- Personal access tokens
- Local database URLs
- Personal configuration

Example:
{
  "env": {
    "MY_API_KEY": "your-key-here",
    "LOCAL_DB_URL": "postgresql://localhost:5433/mydb"
  }
}

PERSONAL TOOL PREFERENCES:
- Editor settings
- Shell preferences
- Tool-specific config

Example:
{
  "env": {
    "EDITOR": "vim",
    "MY_PREFERRED_SHELL": "zsh"
  }
}

SECURITY NOTE
=============

This file is gitignored by default, so it's safe to put secrets here.
However, be careful:
- Don't share this file
- Keep backups if needed
- Don't commit it accidentally

DIFFERENCE FROM SETTINGS.JSON
=============================

settings.json (shared):
- Team-wide permissions
- Project-wide env vars
- Shared configuration
- Committed to git

settings.local.json (personal):
- Your personal permissions
- Your personal env vars
- Your machine-specific settings
- Not committed (gitignored)

PRECEDENCE
==========

Settings are merged in this order (later overrides earlier):
1. settings.json (team defaults)
2. settings.local.json (your overrides)
3. Command line arguments

So your settings.local.json values take precedence over team settings.

EXAMPLE COMPLETE CONFIG
=======================

{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-settings.json",
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "Bash(my-custom-build-script)"
    ]
  },
  "env": {
    "MY_PERSONAL_API_KEY": "xxx",
    "LOCAL_TEST_DB": "postgresql://localhost:5433/test"
  }
}

CREATING THIS FILE
==================

1. Copy this template to .claude/settings.local.json
2. Add your personal settings
3. That's it - it's automatically gitignored

The file will be loaded automatically on next Claude Code start.
*/
